  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to Set Up of the Common Shelter/Non-Food Item (NFI) Pipeline to Respond to the Needs of Internally Displaced People (IDPs) in Northern Mozambique</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The conflict in Northern Mozambique caused more than 745,000 Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) who are in need of emergency assistance. Through the contribution to the IOM Emergency Common Pipeline System, the Swiss Agency for Development and Cooperation (SDC) is supporting the provision of timely and quality materials for shelter construction and non-food items, thus increasing resilience of up to 25,000 IDPs (mainly children and women) to adverse climate events. Through prepositioned stocks in the IOM common pipeline system, procurement of the humanitarian actors&#x2019; time will be cut of 4-5 month, hence speeding up recovery.</narrative>
  </description>
